{"TopicId":166453,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Angle snap for docking ports?","CreatedByName":"Kergarin","CreatedById":153808,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-10-12T17:16:00Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Kergarin","CreatedById":153808,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-10-12T17:16:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello,\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen building something in orbit it\u0027s often important to dock the parts precisely together, and sometimes it\u0027s hard to see if they are a few degrees off or not.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo what about an option for docking ports where they only snap in to each other at fixed steps like every 5 or 10 degrees when activated?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think that would be really helpfull.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-10-12T20:40:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis was pretty much the first thing I asked when I joined.\u00A0 It would be great if it worked into stock, but hopefully this will get you by.\u00A0 Not only will it snap to a variety of angles, but it lets you weld the parts together if it\u0027s going to be permanent.\u00A0 First mod I even installed:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed9572789908\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/149233-13-konstruction-weldable-ports-servos-cranes-and-magnets-013/\u0026amp;\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:214px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klgraham1013","CreatedById":105132,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-10-12T21:25:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can also make a simple \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Module Manager (mod)\u0022\u003EMM\u003C/abbr\u003E config, you don\u0027t want to use all of Konstruction.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FungusForge","CreatedById":148313,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-10-13T17:16:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://spacedock.info/mod/870/SnapDock\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ESnapdock\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0is one such \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Module Manager (mod)\u0022\u003EMM\u003C/abbr\u003E config, in case you don\u0027t want to write one yourself.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tyko","CreatedById":164179,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-10-13T17:42:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223194062\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166453\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221507914962\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022148313\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FungusForge\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n25 minutes ago, FungusForge said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://spacedock.info/mod/870/SnapDock\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ESnapdock\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0is one such \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Module Manager (mod)\u0022\u003EMM\u003C/abbr\u003E config, in case you don\u0027t want to write one yourself.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u002B1 for Snapdock. It works great.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}